HEADWORD: Corb
<hw>Corb</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧rb)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>corbis</ets> basket. Cf. <er>Corbeil</er>, <er>Corp</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A basket used in coal mines, etc. see
<er>Corf</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>An ornament in a building; a
corbel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corban</ent>⟦br⟧
